OL,3,CNorthern Ireland reacts to
OL,4,Cchancellor's Spring Statement
OL,6,F"The DUP has consistently warned that
OL,7,Fbusiness is being taxed to death, yet
OL,8,Fthe Government refuses to acknowledge
OL,9,Fthe impact of its policies. Once
OL,10,Fagain, today's Statement offers no
OL,11,Frecognition of the damage inflicted by
OL,12,Frising business tax bills, nor does it
OL,13,Fset out a credible plan for economic
OL,14,Fgrowth.
OL,16,F"This was a chance to reset - an
OL,17,Fopportunity to inspire confidence -
OL,18,Fbut instead, it is yet another missed
OL,19,Fopportunity."
