OL,3,CNorthern Ireland reacts to
OL,4,Cchancellor's Spring Statement
OL,6,FSuzanne Wylie, Chief Executive of the,
OL,7,FNI Chamber said: "After 9 in 10 of our
OL,8,Fmembers found themselves under
OL,9,Fpressure to raise prices because of
OL,10,Fthe Autumn Budget, it is welcome that
OL,11,Fthere are no further tax rises in
OL,12,Ftoday's Spring Statement.
OL,14,F"Business urgently needs an injection
OL,15,Fof confidence to drive investment and
OL,16,Fstimulate growth. While instilling
OL,17,Fthat confidence against a backdrop of
OL,18,Fgeopolitical uncertainty and rising
OL,19,Ffiscal pressures is not an easy task,
OL,20,Fwe need government to be courageous in
OL,21,Fdriving economic momentum."
